2. Point Class

A Point represents a point in 2D space.

Example:

class Point:
    def __init__(self, x, y):
        self.x_cod = x
        self.y_cod = y

    def __str__(self):
        return '<{},{}>'.format(self.x_cod, self.y_cod)
Explanation
class Point:

This creates a new data type called Point.

def __init__(self, x, y):

This is the constructor. It runs automatically when we create an object.

self.x_cod = x
self.y_cod = y

These are object attributes. Every point will have its own x and y coordinates.

def __str__(self):

This method decides how the object will look when printed.

Example:

p1 = Point(3, 4)
print(p1)

Output:

<3,4>
3. Line Class

A line can be represented using the equation:

Ax + By + C = 0

Example:

class Line:
    def __init__(self, A, B, C):
        self.A = A
        self.B = B
        self.C = C

    def __str__(self):
        return '{}x + {}y + {} = 0'.format(self.A, self.B, self.C)

Example:

l1 = Line(1, 2, 3)
print(l1)

Output:

1x + 2y + 3 = 0
