29. Final Revision Summary

This session mainly teaches that OOP is not only about creating classes and objects. It is about designing safe, reusable, and realistic systems.

The most important ideas are:

Object = real-world entity
Reference variable = variable pointing to object
Encapsulation = protecting object data
Private variable = hidden variable using __
Getter = safely read data
Setter = safely update data
Instance variable = object-level variable
Static variable = class-level shared variable
Static method = class utility method

